<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="U." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="U. kondorosyi" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kondorosyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">U. kondorosyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of the genus by the entirely blackish pronotum decorated with small ochraceous spots at humeral angles; irregular brownish spots covering most of the corium; confluent pronotal callosities; and a narrow impunctate band at the posterior edge of pronotum, widened at humeral angles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Distributed across New Guinea and adjacent islands. The species inhabits mostly rainforests, but records from mangroves and grasslands are available too.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
